<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>hold a job • hold down a job</xh5><p> <i>hold a job—</i>have a job; be employed: The number of unemployed workers who had not <u>held a job</u> in over twelve months nearly doubled in the 1990s.</p><p> <i>hold down a job—</i>keep a job for a reasonable length of time: He never <u>held a job down</u> for long because of the drink, he was always getting sacked.</p> </entry>
